               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481023-name-1222" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1222" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1222" type="surname" value="POOLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1222" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM POOLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker, and have one partner. On 11th Oct. the prisoner came to our house, and I saw her take down a gown, and conceal it beneath her clothes, and a bundle of sheets, and put them under her shawl—she left the shop, saying she would call again in the afternoon—I followed her, and asked her to walk back with me, and I saw her drop these things from under her shawl, and from under her petticoats—I had not sold them to her—she had no right to them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I had had a little too much to drink, and he <hi rend="italic">chaffed</hi> roe; I could not have-stolen them; I beg for mercy, on account of my poor children; I never was in the hands of a policeman but once before; I have worked nine years for one master.</p>
